page.title: 09Family pets
page.content: In a survey we found that the majority of people had pets,62% in fact.The most common pets were fish with a total of 137,78 of which were tropical fish.The rarest animals were the 2 ducks.There were 80 dogs which were the second most common.The cats came next with a total of 32,ferrets came to more than expected with 22.There were 6 different types of rodents:7 hamsters, 7 gerbils,3 mice and 13 rabbits.There were also 4 tortoise and 5 terrapins. 3 frogs and 7 birds also appeared on our list.Ninety people shared a total of 312 pets between them.Some people obviously had more than 1 pet.
